BindHelp is a tool to take a folder full of files and
turn them into a StrongHelp Manual.

It is invoked with:

BindHelp <SourceDir> <DestFile> [options]
  options: -f - use appended filetypes
           -r - use existing !Root
           -v - verbose


BindHelp was created by Tony van der Hoff
and modified by Stephen Fryatt.

It is a tool developed and supplied with the OSLib
project.

The source code for this project can be found in the
OSLib source code.


